1 boaters, state natural resource agencies, and the United States Fish and Wildlife Service
2 has resulted in the most successful model of fisheries management in the world, restoring
3 and enhancing fish populations across the United States and its territories; and
4 WHEREAS, since 1939, the combined contribution of the Wildlife and Sport Fish
5 Restoration Programs and license fees to the state fish and wildlife agencies exceeds $78
6 billion dollars which is more than any other single conservation effort in American
7 history and constitutes, collectively, the American system of conservation funding;
8 NOW, THEREFORE,
9 Be it resolved by the Senate of the General Assembly of the Commonwealth of
10 Kentucky, the House of Representatives concurring therein:
11 Section 1. The General Assembly recognizes America's anglers and boaters, the
12 sportfishing industry, state fish and wildlife agencies, and the United States Fish and
13 Wildlife Service for their leading role in restoring healthy populations of fish and aquatic
14 resources, both game and non-game, to the abundance we see today, and with the help of
15 the Sport Fish Restoration Program, in this 75th year of the program's establishment that
16 is the model for the American system of conservation funding.
17 Section 2. The Clerk of the Senate is directed to transmit a copy of this
18 Resolution to the Kentucky Department of Fish and Wildlife Resources and the offices of
19 the members of Kentucky's congressional delegation. Those receiving this Resolution are
20 encouraged to further its dissemination to local, regional, and national medial sources so
21 that all may know and appreciate the foresight and contributions from anglers, the
22 sportfishing industry, state fish and wildlife agencies, and the United States Fish and
23 Wildlife Service on behalf of our nation's fisheries and aquatic resources.
